SUMMARY IN SUPPORT OF SENATE BILL 94

If Senate Bill 94 passes with the attached proposed amendments,

who will be included in its protections?

1.

All elderly persons who are mentally retarded, mentally
ill (but not involuntarily committed or committed for

a criminal act), and physically handicapped will be
included in the protections of Senate Bill 94 and
therefore permitted to live in group homes.

All mentally retarded persons will be permitted to live
in group homes.

All physically handicapped persons will be permitted

to live in group homes.

All dependent children will be permitted to live in
group homes.

